ssh-keygen -t rsa
• Generates an SSH key pair (public key + private key).
• Keys are usually saved in ~/.ssh/id_rsa (private) and ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub (public).

ssh-copy-id publickey username@ip
• Copies the public key to the remote server.
• Adds the key to the remote user’s ~/.ssh/authorized_keys file.
• Enables passwordless (key-based) SSH login.

ssh username@ip -i privatekeypath
• Connects to the remote server using a specific private key.
• Used when the private key is not in the default location.
